<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Laurianne Martinez-S&egrave;ve, &ldquo;Les coroplathes de Suse, statut des artisans d&rsquo;une ville hell&eacute;nis&eacute;e,&rdquo; <em>Topoi</em> 8/2, 1998, pp. 653-56. Margaret Christina Miller, <em>Athens and Persia in the Fifth Century B.C.: A Study of Cultural Receptivity</em>, Cambridge, 1997. Carl Nylander, &ldquo;Clamps and Chronology (Achaemenid Problems II),&rdquo; <em>Iranica Antiqua</em> 6, 1966, pp. 130-46. Idem, &ldquo;Foreign Craftsmen in Achaemenid Persia,&rdquo; in Akbar Tajvidi and Mohammad-Yusof Kiani, eds., <em>The Memorial Volume of theVth International Congress of Iranian Art and Archaeology: Tehran, Isfahan, Shiraz 11th-18th April 1968</em>, Tehran, 1351 &Scaron;./1972, 2 vols., I, pp. 311-18. Idem, <em>Ionians in Pasargadae: Studies in Old Persian Architecture</em>, Uppsala, 1970. Idem, &ldquo;Anatolians in Susa&mdash;and Persepolis(?),&rdquo; <em>Monumentum H. S. Nyberg</em>, Acta Iranica 6, Tehran and Li&egrave;ge, 1975, pp. 317-23. Idem, &ldquo;Achaemenid Imperial Art,&rdquo; in Mogens Trolle Larsen, ed., <em>Power and Propaganda: A Symposium on Ancient Empires</em>, Mesopotamia 7, Copenhagen 1979a, pp. 345-59. Idem, &ldquo;Mason&rsquo;s Marks in Persepolis<em>,&rdquo; Akten des VII Internationalen Kongress f&uuml;r Iranische Kunst und Arch&auml;ologie, M&uuml;nchen 7-10 September 1976</em>, AMI Erg&auml;nzungband 6, 1979b, pp. 236-39. Idem, &ldquo;A Foot-Note from Persepolis,&rdquo; <em>Anadolu/Anatolia </em>22, 1981-83, pp. 57-68. M. Rahbar, &ldquo;Kāve&scaron;-e bāstān-&scaron;enāsi dar Gelālak &Scaron;u&scaron;tar,&rdquo; in Maḥmud Mu-sawi, ed., <em>Yād-nāma-ye gerd-e ham-āyi-e bāstān-&scaron;enāsi-e &Scaron;u&scaron;</em>, Tehran, 1997, pp. 175-208. Idem, &ldquo;Khorheh, une r&eacute;sidence d&rsquo;&eacute;poque parthe sur le Plateau iranien,&rdquo; <em>Dossiers d&rsquo;arch&eacute;ologie</em> 243, 1999a, pp. 44-46. Idem, &ldquo;Pažuhe&scaron;-i dar bāra-ye yak mojassama-ye marmari-e yunāni az Borāzjān,&rdquo; in ʿAbbās ʿAlizāda, Yusof Majidzāda, and Ṣādeq Malek &Scaron;ahmirzādi, <em>Bāstān-&scaron;enāsi o honar-e Irāŋ/The Iranian World: Essays on Iranian Art and Archaeology Presented to Ezzat O. Negahban</em>, Tehran, 1999b, pp. 192-207. Gisela M. A. Richter, &ldquo;Greeks in Persia,&rdquo; <em>AJA </em>50, 1946, 15-30. Idem, &ldquo;Greek Subjects on &lsquo;Graeco-Persian&rsquo; Seal Stones,&rdquo; in George C. Miles, ed., <em>Archaeologica Orientalia in Memoriam Ernst Herzfeld</em>, New York, 1952, pp. 189&ndash;94. Michael D. Roaf and John Boardman, &ldquo;A Greek Painting at Persepolis,&rdquo; <em>Journal of Hellenic Studies</em> 100, 1980, pp. 204&ndash;6. Margaret Cool Root, <em>The King and Kingship in Achaemenid Art: Essays on the Creation of an Iconography of Empire</em>, Acta Iranica 19, Leiden, 1979. Idem, &ldquo;Pyramidal Stamp Seals&mdash;The Persepolis Connection,&rdquo; in Maria Brosius and Amelie Kurt, eds., <em>Achaemenid History XI: Essays in Memory of David M. Lewis</em>, Leiden, 1998, pp. 257&ndash;89. Daniel Schlumberger, <em>L&rsquo;Orient hell&eacute;nis&eacute;: L&rsquo;art grec et ses h&eacute;ritiers dans l&rsquo;Asie non m&eacute;diterran&eacute;enne</em>, Paris, 1970. Erich Friedrich Schmidt, <em>Persepolis II</em>, Oriental Institute Publications 69, Chicago, 1957. Mark Aurel Stein, &ldquo;An Archaeological Tour in Ancient Persia,&rdquo; <em>Iraq </em>3, 1936, pp. 111&ndash;225. Idem, <em>Old Routes of Western Iran: Narrative of an Archaeological Journey</em>, London, 1940, pp. 130&ndash;59. Marie-Joseph Steve, &ldquo;Inscriptions des Ach&eacute;m&eacute;nides &agrave; Suse,&rdquo; <em>Stud. Ir</em>. 3/1, 1974, pp. 7&ndash;28, 2, pp. 135&ndash;69. David Stronach, <em>Pasargadae</em>: <em>A Report on the Excavations Conducted by the Institute of Persian Studies from 1961 to 1963</em>, Oxford, 1978. A. Uchitel, &ldquo;Foreign Workers in the Fortification Archive,&rdquo; in Leon de Meyer and Hermann Gasche, eds., <em>M&eacute;sopotamia et Elam:Actes de la XXXVIe